{# 
    Base Font (<basefont>)
    ===========================================================================
    Specifies a default font size, color, and face for all the text in a document.

    Variables:
    - `basefont_size`: The default font size. Defaults to "3".
    - `basefont_color`: The default font color. Defaults to "black".
    - `basefont_face`: The default font face. Defaults to "Arial".

    Notes:
    - The <basefont> tag is deprecated in HTML5 and should not be used.
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/basefont
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_basefont.asp

#}

<basefont 
    size="{{ basefont_size | default('3') | e }}" 
    color="{{ basefont_color | default('black') | e }}" 
    face="{{ basefont_face | default('Arial') | e }}"
>
